Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Frontend Engineer position with Luma AI. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack web applications, AI-native interfaces, and experiment-driven product development, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across multiple engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the technical depth and user-centric focus this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I built production-ready interfaces translating natural-language intents into validated tool calls across 1,000+ endpoints — requiring rigorous component design, state management, and safe execution patterns for AI-native experiences. I developed generative code solutions (API-aware templates, SDK patterns, code-generation workflows) that improved documentation and implementation correctness through clean component patterns and thoughtful abstractions. To ensure these systems remained reliable and performant, I architected an observability layer using Langfuse and LangSmith for tracing, structured logs, and evaluation hooks to monitor behavior and track metrics. I also ran growth experiments optimizing routing and concurrency, reducing latency by 60% and API costs by 50% through performance optimization and experiment-driven iteration focused on engagement — directly mirroring the rapid prototyping and metrics-driven approach central to this role. Throughout this work, I partnered closely with product and design teams to architect concurrent multi-agent orchestration using LangChain and LangGraph, demonstrating my ability to collaborate across functions and translate product requirements into scalable, production-ready interfaces. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform using React, Spring Boot, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications with a focus on scalable design system and frontend architecture. I also built an internal support chatbot using LangChain and RAG with PostgreSQL vector store, improving onboarding and reducing ticket resolution time by 20% — giving me hands-on experience building user-facing features that improve conversion and engagement. Together, these roles have prepared me to contribute meaningfully to the Dream Machine web application and growth engineering surfaces, delivering high-quality interfaces that serve millions of users.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in AI systems, technical communication, and collaborative problem-solving — skills that translate directly into the innovation-driven, creator-centric culture Luma AI values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion to generate fashion designs using CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on Pace's HPC cluster, giving me deep exposure to the kind of multimodal AI systems Luma AI is building. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on GPU programming with CUDA and Mojo, and on building AI Agents with LangChain, LangGraph, and LangSmith for an audience of 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring the collaborative, knowledge-sharing culture this team values. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor, communicates with clarity, and thrives in fast-paced, research-to-product environments.

I have always been passionate about building multimodal general intelligence and expanding human imagination through vision-based AI, and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of Luma AI's mission to create intelligent creative partners that interact with the physical world. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

